<TEXT>
herbert h schiller an assistant postmaster 
general for technology who helped advance automation and technology 
developments in mail delivery has died 
schiller who was 62 died of cancer on friday at george 
washington university hospital 
a native of vienna austria schiller came to the united states 
in his youth and worked for the sperryrand corp and harris corp 
before serving as technical director for international telephone 
and telegraph corp he joined the us postal service in 1983 
under his direction the postal service initiated technological 
developments in optical scanning and document handling one of 
schillers innovations the automated postal teller will undergo 
customer testing later this year 
schiller is also credited with establishing a technological 
development advisory board of outside academic and industry 
professionals at the postal service and initiated an annual 
advanced technology conference 
a resident of fairfax va schiller was born in austria and 
emigrated to the united states in the 1930s after serving in the 
army in world war ii schiller was graduated from carnegiemellon 
university and received a masters degree in electrical engineering 
from columbia university 
he is survived by his wife julia and a daughter margaret ann 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

