<TEXT>
the folks in lake wobegon must be 
wondering what in the world has gotten into that boy garrison 
keillor has taken to the city 
a prairie home companion the most popular show on public 
radio is coming back temporarily but the endless cornfields are 
shadowed by skyscrapers and all those norwegian bachelor farmers 
are rubbing elbows with the homeless 
one year after it ended its 13year run keillors uniquely 
personal show will be broadcast next saturday from new yorks radio 
