young arabs threw stones and bottles at the army headquarters and 
soldiers responded with tear gas grenades and rubber bullets said 
an arab journalist speaking on condition of anonymity no injuries 
were reported 
several palestinians were ordered to park their vehicles in 
front of the army headquarters to prevent more attacks he said 
in the shati refugee camp the army ordered a curfew requiring 
people to stay at home and a commercial strike paralyzed gaza 
city young palestinians stoned stoned cars and set tires ablaze 
the protests occurred the day after a 3yearold palestinian 
girl died in gaza city relatives said she died of tear gas 
inhalation after israeli soldiers threw tear gas grenades but 
hospital officials said the army confirmed the death without giving 
a cause 
at least 198 arabs have been killed since violence began dec 8 
among the 15 million palestinians of the west bank and gaza strip 
which israel captured from jordan and egypt in the 1967 middle east 
war an israeli soldier and a jewish settler also have been slain 
some residents of arura complained to authorities about being 
stoned beaten and burned with cigarettes when troops raided the 
village north of ramallah on may 18 
villagers told associated press reporter karin laub earlier this 
week that the raid on arura which its 2000 residents have 
declared liberated started at 5 am with 40 to 50 army 
vehicles two helicopters and a gravelfiring device 
mohammed awad 23 who had a swollen ankle handcuffs marks on 
his wrists and a blue mark on his right eye said he was captured 
by israeli troops and ordered to sit in a hilltop stone pit 
he said hassan salah 22 and mohammed zeid 29 were forced to 
sit in similar sixfootdeep pits nearby 
there were about 20 to 25 soldiers who threw stones at me and 
the others awad said it went on for two hours 
awad said he was then taken with 12 other detainees to ramallah 
prison and on the way soldiers threw burning cigarettes on them 
he said troops extinquished cigarettes on bilal mahmoud 19 
daoud suleiman farradni a ramallah hospital doctor who lives in 
the village said he examined mahmoud after the event and found 
eight to ten cigarette burns on his chest and ankles 
on awad the doctor said 
his face was swollen and covered with bruises there were also 
bruises and swelling on his waist and legs either from stones or 
clubs 
earlier this week the military command said an initial 
investigation was made at the site and no evidence was found to 
support the allegations on saturday the army said it will 
launch another probe 
a senior official at the military administration said the army 
was scheduled to open secondary schools which cover grades 69 on 
sunday and high schools will open june 6 
at the height of the rebellion in february the military 
government closed 1200 schools in the west bank and gaza strip 
shutting out more than 300000 students schools in gaza have 
operated onandoff since 
schools had been major centers of protest in the first two 
months of the uprising 
underground leaders of the 6monthold palestinian rebellion 
issued a new leaflet calling for a general strike monday and a 
strike june 36 to protest the expected visit of us secretary of 
state george p shultz 
