the leftist government and rebel 
leaders suspended peace talks saturday but agreed to maintain a 
current truce at least until the two sides meet again in 10 days 
gen humberto ortega the head of the government delegation 
blamed enrique bermudez the rebel military commander for the 
failure to reach a definitive ceasefire agreement during the three 
days of talks 
a spokesman for the rebel delegation in managua said the 
compromise suspension came after the rebels rejected a 
government proposal for a 30day ceasefire extension a plan for 
delivering humanitarian aid to rebel units and a new round of 
talks starting on june 15 
