development of new fighter planes a newspaper reported saturday 
the nationally circulated yomiuri shimbun quoting anonymous 
japanese government sources said workinglevel officials from the 
two governments reached the agreement friday night in a meeting at 
the defense agency 
japanese defense officials were not available for comment 
saturday 
there were no figures for the development costs but an initial 
order of 100 of the new jets is estimated at 8 billion 
the officials started their latest series of talks tuesday on 
the proposed joint development of japans nextgeneration fighter 
plane the fsx the report said 
tokyo and washington have debated us participation in the 
project since 1986 
japan first sought to develop the jet using its own technology 
while us officials pressed for a joint project following a 
series of negotiations japan decided last year to base the fsx 
development on general dynamics corps f16 fighter 
the newspaper said the two sides also agreed in principle that 
technological information gained in the research and development of 
the plane would be shared by the two countries 
details of the joint development will be exchanged in june when 
us defense secretary frank carlucci visits tokyo for talks with 
the director general of the defense agency tsutomu kawara the 
report said 
