<TEXT>
robert f kennedy was shot 20 years ago 
as dozens of people stood within arms reach of the assassin yet 
even with all those witnesses many still insist there was more to 
it than the solitary act of the gunman 
the fbi and the los angeles police department have concluded the 
murder was the work of one man 
but conspiracy theorists point to incomplete police files and 
suggest that a second gunman fired at kennedy from behind while 
sirhan sirhan stood in front of him they cite witnesses who 
claimed that sirhan was seen with an unidentified young woman in a 
polka dot dress shortly before the shooting 
those believing in conspiracy turn up regularly at a small 
walledoff section of the southeastern massachusetts university 
library home of the robert f kennedy assassination archives the 
largest collection of its kind 
the majority of people who come to us for information already 
embrace a notion of conspiracy of some kind said phillip h 
melanson a political science professor at the university who also 
heads the archives 
the archives contain the 10000page transcript of sirhans 
trial and thousands of pages of district attorneys files melanson 
and his staff have 8000 pages of the recently declassified 
32000page fbi file of the investigation into the murder and are 
getting the rest add to those 600 hours of audio tape and 5000 
newspaper clippings 
melanson believes sirhan did not act alone he and other 
scholars have been critical of the los angeles police 
investigation suggesting it was haphazard and resulted in the 
destruction of key evidence 
in april melanson said only 400 hours of testimony remained 
preserved on tape in los angeles police files although 
investigators earlier had spoken of thousands of hours of taped 
interviews 
history may have dictated keeping those longer but i was not 
consulted said tom reddin los angeles police chief at the time 
of the assassination who dismisses suggestions of a coverup 
the question you have to ask he said is what the devil 
are we trying to cover up 
his deepest regret reddin said is that someone did not step in 
to keep kennedy from entering the ambassador hotel kitchen where 
sirhan lay in wait 
kennedys entourage insisted on no police protection for his 
appearances in los angeles and no police were present at the 
hotel asked whether the police should have disregarded the 
request reddin said sadly i dont think we should have but i 
wish we did 
even melanson acknowledged that some of those who share his view 
that sirhan did not act alone lack convincing arguments 
certainly there is a group of people who embrace conspiracy 
out of perhaps devotion to the political figure said melanson 
social scientist john clarke of the university of arizona at 
tucson perceived psychological needs behind conspiracy theories 
noting the charismatic appeal of leaders like rfk and his 
brother john f kennedy clarke said thats why a certain number 
of people dont want to let these people go and this curiosity 
about who killed these people is one handle they have on that 
for a tragedy of such magnitude it may be only natural to 
question simple explanations there has got to be a much more 
elaborate background of conspiracy the common error lies in making 
more complex what are simple events said franklin l ford a 
harvard university history professor 
added ford author of political murder from tyrannicide to 
terrorism it is possible to order a mailorder highvelocity 
rifle to kill the president of the united states but the public 
doesnt accept that 
