tightening credit to slow the economy down 
stocks fell on wall street where the dow jones average of 30 
industrials dropped 1031 points to 195644 finishing the week 
with a net gain of 385 points volume was light 
in the bond market a key barometer of interestrate trends 
prices ended largely mixed after falling earlier in the day many 
traders quit early for the long memorial day weekend 
economists who had worried that the october stock crash foretold 
a recession have since expressed surprise at the countrys surging 
economic growth as signaled by low unemployment surging exports 
and strains on productive capacities 
the latest survey of the national association of business 
economists released friday showed a substantial upward revision in 
growth estimates for this year compared with a survey done three 
months ago 
the economists who advise some of the countrys largest 
corporations said they were looking for the gross national product 
to expand 29 percent this year which would match the performance 
turned in during 1986 and 1987 
on thursday the government to revise its own estimate of 
overall economic growth to 39 percent for the first three months 
of the year instead of 23 percent 
